com.flopsar.fdbc.api

Interface FindEvent<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of an object to be passed on event.

    public interface FindEvent<T>
    A user must implement this interface so that they can process data that are passed in the onFound(Object). method.
    Since:
    2.3

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean onFound(T object)
      A callback method that is called whenever an object is found.

    • Method Detail

      • onFound

        boolean onFound(T object)
        A callback method that is called whenever an object is found. Whether the calling thread is executed or not can be controlled by the return value of this method. If the execution should be stopped the method must return true.
        Parameters:
        object - a T object to be passed.
        Returns:
        true if the caller should be stopped, otherwise false if the caller should continue.
        Since:
        2.3
